1. cs.IT (Information Theory) - The paper deals with the achievable rate per user with zero forcing, which is a fundamental concept in information theory. 
2. cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) - The paper studies strategies for transferring CSI to the central processing unit, which is a key aspect of networking and internet architecture. 
3. cs.SY (Systems and Control) - The paper deals with the design and analysis of a system for uplink transmission in cell-free massive MIMO, which falls under the purview of systems and control. 
4. cs.MM (Multimedia) - The paper deals with the transmission of data in a wireless network, which is a key aspect of multimedia systems. 
5. cs.COM (Computers and Society) - This category is less likely, but the paper may have implications for the design and deployment of wireless networks, which could have societal implications.
